</ul>

<h2>Investment Style Profiles</h2>

<h3>The "Passive Investor"</h3>

<p><strong>Characteristics:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Full-time job or business commitments</li>
<li>Property is one of many investments</li>
<li>Values time over marginal cost savings</li>
<li>Wants predictable, passive income</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Best Choice:</strong> <strong>Full-Service Management</strong></p>

<p><strong>Why:</strong> Your time is worth more than what you'd save with bare management. Full-service generates significantly higher revenue that compounds over time.</p>

<h3>The "Hands-On Investor"</h3>

<p><strong>Characteristics:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Lives in or near Melaka</li>
<li>Enjoys learning the business</li>
<li>Wants to understand every aspect</li>
<li>Has time and interest for involvement</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Best Choice:</strong> <strong>Bare Management OR Full-Service</strong></p>

<p><strong>Why:</strong> If you truly enjoy the work, bare management saves money. But be honest about your time commitment - most hands-on investors underestimate the workload.</p>

<h3>The "Portfolio Investor"</h3>

<p><strong>Characteristics:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Owns or plans 3+ properties</li>
<li>Scalability is key concern</li>
<li>Wants systems, not manual processes</li>
<li>Focuses on ROI, not involvement</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Best Choice:</strong> <strong>Full-Service Management</strong></p>

<p><strong>Why:</strong> Scaling beyond 1-2 properties with bare management is impossible. Full-service scales efficiently - you can own 10+ properties with minimal time.</p>

<h3>The "Hybrid Investor"</h3>

<p><strong>Characteristics:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Wants passive income but some control</li>
<li>Interested in learning but not doing</li>
<li>Likes transparency and reporting</li>
